Reasoning: The paper deals with interference coordination and optimization in millimeter-wave communication networks, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of non-homogeneous waterfilling and stream control also suggests a focus on signal processing and communication theory (cs.MM). The paper also proposes fast-converging coordination algorithms, which may fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the relevance of the findings to 5G New Radio suggests a possible connection to computer communications (cs.COM).
